	('3a219931-4044-4ce5-9418-00204aaf8f7b', 'reading', 5, 'The annual dinner at Smith & Co. typically starts with a _____ speech by the CEO.', 'welcome', 'opening', 'concluding', 'keynote', NULL, 'D', 3, 'The correct answer is D, as the context suggests a formal speech that sets the tone for the evening.', '2025-09-23 14:58:32.582561', '2025-09-23 14:58:32.582581', 'syntax', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('604a7495-d080-41e9-b58d-0026e399f393', 'reading', 6, '4. Which phrase correctly completes the last blank?', 'centering on', 'pertaining to', 'getting along with', 'regarding', NULL, 'C', 2, '這裡的空格需要填入一個表示團隊合作的重要性的詞，因此 \'getting along with\' 是正確的選擇。', '2025-09-21 17:30:26.000000', '2025-09-21 17:30:26.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'b5763c74-5d1d-47c0-8044-70d0e7eb77a5', NULL),
	('45801521-8c9e-44f2-96f7-00883f4f7991', 'reading', 5, 'The company\'s recent survey revealed that most employees are satisfied with their jobs _____ they were hired.', 'since', 'until', 'once', 'as soon as', NULL, 'D', 3, '選項 D "as soon as" 是正確答案，因為它們是對於兩個事件的關係，表示某件事發生在另一件事之前。其他選項都無法表達這種關係。', '2025-09-04 16:00:39.591496', '2025-09-04 16:00:39.591513', 'syntax', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('f27c91c5-7154-4003-b777-00a96d50a01f', 'listen', 2, 'What is the main objective of the new market research?', 'To improve product features.', 'To identify customer preferences.', 'To increase advertising spending.', NULL, NULL, 'B', 3, '這題的正確答案是B。"To identify customer preferences" 是新市場研究的主要目的，而選項A的產品特性改善與選項C的增加廣告支出雖然相關，但並不直接符合問題中詢問的主要目標。', '2025-09-04 17:23:43.000000', '2025-09-04 17:23:43.000000', 'business', '475ef8cc-8de3-43aa-8d6b-f9b2215534bf', NULL, NULL),
	('9039e640-5f11-4242-b58d-00c0c070abfe', 'reading', 6, '1. What is the purpose of this luncheon?', 'to celebrate an anniversary', 'to discuss projects', 'to conduct interviews', 'to finalize contracts', NULL, 'B', 2, '這個午餐會的目的主要是為了網絡交流和討論未來的計畫。', '2025-09-21 00:30:22.000000', '2025-09-21 00:30:22.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '9ba7bc25-2833-4053-b770-18c6fa66a2b3', NULL),
	('a7c622c1-a8b5-4fb9-bcfa-00d2b9a4a430', 'reading', 6, 'Your reports should be __2__ so that everyone can easily understand your points.', 'clear', 'clearly', 'clarity', 'clearer', NULL, 'A', 1, '此空格描述報告的質量，選擇 A 的 \'clear\' 是正確的形容詞形式，用於修飾 reports。', '2025-09-22 20:00:22.000000', '2025-09-22 20:00:22.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '0df7001a-72fa-40e2-a07b-c4e850787858', NULL),
	('49ceaa5c-0e86-4d87-bac5-00f4b6ffbda0', 'reading', 6, 'What is the appropriate word for blank 3?', 'Communicating', 'Responding', 'Focusing', 'Adding', NULL, 'C', 3, '這句話強調要針對現有客戶進行明確集中，因此 “Focusing” 是最合適的詞。', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '31aa1954-802c-44f6-bfa4-ba9a92ad9a79', NULL),
	('6fdb5bc1-a7eb-4a08-9042-012f9392c580', 'reading', 5, 'The company has a policy of _______________ all employees who have been with the firm for over five years.', 'retaining', 'retain', 'to retain', 'retainingly', NULL, 'A', 3, '本題目考查《句子》中的被动语态（passive voice），選項 A«retaining»正確，因為公司有政策保留所有已經在公司工作超過五年的人員。', '2025-09-23 10:00:41.358039', '2025-09-23 10:00:41.358058', 'syntax', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('a116fe2e-b0a1-4764-bcba-015fe3cd0495', 'reading', 6, 'What will the marketing team do next week?', 'Launch new products', 'Receive feedback', 'Reach out to clients', 'Organize meetings', NULL, 'C', 2, '題目要求理解行銷團隊接下來的行動，答案C符合文章內容。', '2025-09-22 19:00:31.000000', '2025-09-22 19:00:31.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '53cd8904-de43-4a68-93e7-fc27354dc7c3', NULL),
	('c3cf7408-8651-4ce4-862c-0195779fb618', 'reading', 6, '3. Choose the best verb to complete the sentence.', 'answer', 'respond', 'query', 'questions', NULL, 'A', 2, '在這裡，\'answer\' 是正確的動詞，表示售後團隊需要回答客戶問題。', '2025-09-21 01:00:24.000000', '2025-09-21 01:00:24.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '079c8422-f546-46cd-ab75-5b643ba826ac', NULL),
	('a185feaa-303d-42a2-b643-0282a66822ec', 'reading', 5, 'The new employee has been attending leadership training sessions _____ he started working at the company.', 'since', 'when', 'after', 'before', NULL, 'C', 3, '在這個句子中，使用了完成式（Perfect Continuous）tense，以表示某個事件的開始時間不明確，但是在某個點開始進行某些活動。因此，在這裡選項 C 是正確的，因為它描述了某個點開始進行某些活動，從而使完成式 tense 適用。', '2025-09-04 15:00:39.417492', '2025-09-04 15:00:39.417507', 'tense', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('9b34fc81-4392-4132-b688-02d5083ae2c0', 'reading', 6, 'What should team members do if they have questions?', 'Contact Lisa', 'Wait until the meeting', 'Post on social media', 'Speak to colleagues', NULL, 'A', 2, '文章建議有任何問題應該聯繫Lisa，因此選項A是正確答案。', '2025-09-21 10:00:31.000000', '2025-09-21 10:00:31.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '0c44cbda-e2e4-47a9-be1d-3f7047d8d7ab', NULL),
	('ff3b51f4-7412-49db-a300-02fdc0f1ada8', 'reading', 6, 'What is the appropriate phrase to fill in blank 2?', 'after', 'before', 'during', 'beside', NULL, 'B', 2, '這句話表示我們鼓勵參加者在工作坊之前提交想法，所以正確答案是\'before\'。', '2025-09-22 09:00:32.000000', '2025-09-22 09:00:32.000000', 'syntax', NULL, 'd544453a-64f8-4462-b90c-706e2ff50e10', NULL),
	('18357b8a-f798-4d9b-af9b-037b97f20b1f', 'reading', 6, 'The blank __2__ should be filled with which option?', 'on-site', 'off-site', 'broad', 'limited', NULL, 'A', 2, '這裡應用 \'on-site\' 來表示員工可以在培訓現場直接向技術團隊請教問題。', '2025-09-23 06:30:24.000000', '2025-09-23 06:30:24.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'f01c5c42-eb9c-45e3-ad73-8556f4f9bbe3', NULL),
	('d5fe24d4-b417-4ee9-8dd4-049a91098bfe', 'reading', 5, 'The company\'s new policy requires all employees to submit their expense reports _____ by the end of each quarter.', 'until', 'before', 'since', 'after', NULL, 'B', 3, '本題考察了語句中的「by the end of each quarter」所表達的時間點，要求員工在每個季度結束前提交報表，因此正確答案是 before。', '2025-09-02 06:00:43.372820', '2025-09-02 06:00:43.372840', 'syntax', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('d4eeadf4-142c-4792-85ba-04b455a6528c', 'reading', 6, 'What is the correct word for blank 3?', 'discuss', 'confirm', 'advise', 'speculate', NULL, 'A', 2, '在這裡，\'discuss\' 是合適的選擇，表明參與者會談論和探討任何問題或疑慮。', '2025-09-23 13:30:29.000000', '2025-09-23 13:30:29.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'c5275226-70da-47a0-8a7f-31114953900b', NULL),
	('53beb482-6aae-4693-a6b9-04cf7af81e27', 'reading', 6, '3. included', 'disqualified', 'recognized', 'included', 'excluded', NULL, 'C', 2, '\'Included\' 是正確的選擇，因為要確認你喜好的醫療提供者是否在應保險計劃的範疇內。', '2025-09-23 14:00:33.000000', '2025-09-23 14:00:33.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'ba68d5d0-9a25-45fc-96ae-6a0f21ca4e82', NULL),
	('38279983-1036-46cd-a248-04d5855773f5', 'reading', 5, 'All new patients are required to fill out a medical history form _____ they have their first appointment.', 'before', 'after', 'once', 'while', NULL, 'A', 2, '句子使用一般過去式，表明所有新的病人都需要在他們第一次就診時填寫醫療史資料。', '2025-08-19 05:33:04.398196', '2025-08-19 05:33:04.398790', 'tense', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('e5bca2d3-6db1-47d5-a88c-04d8a999d96f', 'reading', 6, 'When is the information session scheduled?', 'March 15th', 'March 30th', 'April 15th', 'April 30th', NULL, 'B', 2, '根據文章，第2空格提到的資訊會議是在3月30日。', '2025-09-20 17:30:26.000000', '2025-09-20 17:30:26.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '2055db06-ce5e-40ab-ac4b-a036f178619b', NULL),
	('4360680e-adfb-4735-876e-04e1992d3f57', 'reading', 5, 'The new policy requires all employees to disclose their financial interests, except for those who have already _____ the company.', 'joined', 'left', 'resigned', 'retired', NULL, 'B', 3, '句子中使用了except關鍵字，表示除外情況。因此，correct option B \'left\' 是因為已經離職的人員不需要聲明財務利益。', '2025-09-22 10:00:41.287758', '2025-09-22 10:00:41.287770', 'syntax', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('048454c3-8748-484c-a645-050c67172928', 'reading', 6, 'What is the most suitable word to fill in blank 1?', 'updates', 'issues', 'problems', 'solutions', NULL, 'A', 2, '在這裡，\'updates\' 是最合適的選擇，因為它表示更新的功能和改進。', '2025-09-21 23:00:26.000000', '2025-09-21 23:00:26.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '90cc8beb-9a79-4dc8-86b8-78c45c33f4d2', NULL),
	('10c53d1b-a785-4de8-b81e-052934260720', 'listen', 2, 'What is the deadline for submitting the expense reports?', 'Next Friday', 'Next Monday', 'This Friday', NULL, NULL, 'A', 3, '根據公告內容，提交年度報告的截止日為下週五，因此選項A是正確的。', '2025-09-24 01:40:40.000000', '2025-09-24 01:40:40.000000', 'syntax', '8045bd16-0850-4f8e-a066-d9122ed24fd5', NULL, NULL),
	('513fc550-5583-441e-9e95-05555385d23c', 'reading', 6, 'What is the purpose of the brainstorming sessions mentioned?', 'To finalize product designs', 'To generate new ideas', 'To train new employees', 'To review past projects', NULL, 'B', 2, '文中提到所有團隊成員在每週的腦力激盪會議中貢獻想法，因此會議的目的是產生新想法。', '2025-09-21 02:00:33.000000', '2025-09-21 02:00:33.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '654aabe7-b426-4462-8c9b-9ba8741f6c14', NULL),
	('319241ab-89e3-4dfe-8a3d-05c46e6f7367', 'listen', 2, 'What did you think of the new office layout?', 'I think it increased productivity.', 'I prefer the old furniture.', 'Yes, it looks very professional.', NULL, NULL, 'A', 3, '這個問題在詢問對新辦公室佈局的想法。選項A表達對提升生產力的正面看法，B則是對舊家具的偏好，C只是確認新佈局看起來專業。', '2025-09-23 05:30:38.000000', '2025-09-23 05:30:38.000000', 'vocab', 'c43a776e-6046-4d83-b423-770229418960', NULL, NULL),
	('0bdf7b82-270d-4517-8f75-05e9e0b2286f', 'reading', 6, 'Which term is appropriate for blank 2?', 'afterwards', 'immediately', 'gradually', 'later', NULL, 'B', 2, '使用 \'immediately\' 表示我們計劃迅速執行市場策略，這是符合會議主旨的描述。', '2025-09-22 10:30:30.000000', '2025-09-22 10:30:30.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '03cf1b2a-b49c-48ef-ac35-6e18fc0b55d2', NULL),
	('0c6474c5-62a6-4939-ba64-060c668b708a', 'listen', 2, 'When will the new employees start their training?', 'They will begin on Monday.', 'I think it will be helpful.', 'Yes, it\'s in the conference room.', NULL, NULL, 'A', 3, '句子使用未來式 \'will begin\' 來表示新員工的訓練開始時間。選項 B 和 C 的回答並未直接回答問題，故不正確。', '2025-09-21 17:00:37.000000', '2025-09-21 17:00:37.000000', 'pos', '1a4f667f-56f5-4925-9514-c282bb99f93a', NULL, NULL),
	('0ed05198-d342-4eaa-bbdb-062af28c8234', 'reading', 6, 'What should be filled in the blank 3?', 'because', 'before', 'after', 'to', NULL, 'D', 2, '此處的正確用法是「to sign up」，是表示目的的常用結構。', '2025-09-23 02:30:26.000000', '2025-09-23 02:30:26.000000', 'syntax', NULL, '0ac166f4-631d-4ebf-808e-9489ca3707ae', NULL),
	('608022b1-cc03-44c4-a697-066782bb771d', 'reading', 6, 'This is a valuable __4.__ to enhance your skills and knowledge.', 'chance', 'task', 'strategy', 'measure', NULL, 'A', 1, '選擇 A，chance 就是機會的意思，非常合適。', '2025-09-22 08:00:40.000000', '2025-09-22 08:00:40.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '9723ff97-a55f-4fd4-a6a3-c1bdd35661af', NULL),
	('bee5b9c3-1dc9-45ea-8f92-0693a2dd2650', 'reading', 6, 'What fits best in blank 4?', 'refine', 'abandon', 'introduce', 'ignore', NULL, 'A', 3, '根據文章的意思，收集反饋是為了改善或 \'refine\' 我們的策略。', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '31aa1954-802c-44f6-bfa4-ba9a92ad9a79', NULL),
	('dd51b400-a602-429b-813a-06ce6b5420e4', 'listen', 2, 'What is the recommended method for calculating annual taxes for freelancers?', 'You should consult with a tax advisor.', 'It depends on your total earnings.', 'It\'s typically based on hourly rates.', NULL, NULL, 'A', 3, '這題的關鍵在於動詞 \'consult\'，搭配適當的名詞 \'tax advisor\'。選項B與C雖然合理，但沒有給出建議的方法。選項A清晰地指向需要尋求專業的建議。', '2025-09-21 16:04:41.000000', '2025-09-21 16:04:41.000000', 'vocab', '4e690218-014d-4f7a-8ded-6485603a55cf', NULL, NULL),
	('a065710b-3c76-4521-ac3f-07669009065c', 'reading', 6, 'What is the most appropriate word to fill blank 1?', 'integrate', 'expand', 'consider', 'resume', NULL, 'A', 2, '該空格需要一個與融入工作環境相關的動詞，\'integrate\'最為合適。', '2025-09-22 15:00:36.000000', '2025-09-22 15:00:36.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'a5141ec1-7005-4c95-9cbf-1ab1c0fdb92a', NULL),
	('1d99658d-6f42-4822-a0c3-0781a892e674', 'reading', 6, 'What word best fits in blank 2?', 'experience', 'persuasion', 'popularity', 'creativity', NULL, 'A', 2, '在此句中，我們需要形容那些與我們的產品相關的影響者的背景， \'experience\' 是正確的選擇。', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', '2025-09-21 23:30:25.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '31aa1954-802c-44f6-bfa4-ba9a92ad9a79', NULL),
	('ebf26ac1-3997-459c-8ff6-07873f0a2216', 'listen', 2, 'When is the meeting scheduled?', 'Next Monday', 'Next Tuesday', 'This Friday', NULL, NULL, 'B', 3, '題目問的是會議的時間，可從原文中的「next Tuesday at 10 AM」直接得知正確答案是 B。', '2025-09-23 21:00:48.000000', '2025-09-23 21:00:48.000000', 'tense', '8d2344a5-bd31-4d32-a2ab-935c0e8239dd', NULL, NULL),
	('0c56d67e-abbd-408b-8a4f-08bf515dec74', 'reading', 6, 'What type of products are being launched by TechCorp?', 'Innovative devices', 'Outdated models', 'Used equipment', 'Basic tools', NULL, 'A', 2, '本題評估了讀者對於產品類型的理解。根據文章，TechCorp推出的是創新的產品，即使其是新產品。而其他選項的描述則並不符合文意。', '2025-09-22 19:00:31.000000', '2025-09-22 19:00:31.000000', 'vocab', NULL, '53cd8904-de43-4a68-93e7-fc27354dc7c3', NULL),
	('cdf182cb-8111-4d9f-9d08-08c4485648f5', 'reading', 6, 'Which word best fits blank 2?', 'outcomes', 'decisions', 'locations', 'resources', NULL, 'A', 2, '在此句中，空格2 需要使用一個可以表示結果的名詞，而 \'outcomes\' 是最合適的選擇。', '2025-09-21 04:00:30.000000', '2025-09-21 04:00:30.000000', 'vocab', NULL, 'dabdc83f-7232-4f39-ac47-3ed284a1f06d', NULL),
	('ad854d5b-9a3f-4efe-8cdf-08fe7cbca2b9', 'reading', 6, '3. Make sure to contact your insurance provider for any questions regarding __3__ and coverage limits.', 'claims', 'claiming', 'claimed', 'claims-based', NULL, 'A', 2, '在這句中，\'claims\' 是名詞形式，最佳用來指涉保險索賠，故為正確選擇。', '2025-09-23 03:30:25.000000', '2025-09-23 03:30:25.000000', 'pos', NULL, 'e08d2a0a-92df-428d-a504-96c1fddac9a6', NULL),
